# API Routes

- Validate all inputs with **zod** schemas
- Authenticate via Supabase session before any mutation or user-scoped read
- Wrap handlers in try/catch; return typed JSON error responses with appropriate HTTP status codes
- Never leak secrets in error messages

## Patterns

```typescript
const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
if (!user) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Unauthorized" }, { status: 401 });

const body = schema.parse(await request.json());
```

## Route responsibilities

- `POST /api/clients` — create client
- `POST /api/activities` — log interaction + optional expense/deal
- `POST /api/voice/upload` — upload audio to Supabase Storage
- `GET /api/auth/callback` — Supabase OAuth/PKCE callback (safe `next` redirect)
